We are recruiting a Data Scientist to join our IT department.




As a Data Scientist, you will be responsible for:

Collecting, cleaning, and analyzing large datasets from various sources;
Developing and implementing Machine Learning models to solve business problems;
Communicating the results of your analysis in a clear and concise way to stakeholders;
Collaborating with other teams to integrate your models into products and services.




Requirements:

Degree in Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, or a related field;
Practical experience with programming languages such as Python, R, or SQL;
Experience with Machine Learning tools such as scikit-learn, TensorFlow, or PyTorch;
Ability to work independently and as part of a team.




We offer:

Hybrid work arrangement, with the possibility of working in our office in Malta
Annual bonuses based on targets achieved
Wellness services such as psychologist, nutritionist, health and mental coach
Training of your choice




